properties.areaDesc: Gulf waters from East Cape Sable to Chokoloskee 20 to 60 NM out and beyond 5 fathoms; Gulf of Mexico including Dry Tortugas and Rebecca Shoal Channel
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 20 at 4:44AM EST until January 21 at 5:00AM EST by NWS Key West FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds will increase to 15 to 20 knots by sunrise
on Monday, increasing to 20 to 25 knots by Monday evening.
Seas will build to 4 to 8 feet by late Monday.

* WHERE...Gulf waters beyond 5 fathoms including the Dry
Tortugas.

* WHEN...In Effect.

* IMPACTS...A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 20
to 33 knots, or seas of 7 feet or greater, are expected to
produce hazardous conditions for small craft. These hazardous
conditions may result in poor vessel handling and steering
response, broaching, overturned dinghies and kayaks, slips and
falls on slippery decks, rub damage along docks and seawalls,
swamped bows at reef tract mooring balls, and dragging anchors.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The wind increase will occur suddenly due
to passage of a strong cold front.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced boaters, especially those with smaller vessels,
should avoid operating in these conditions.
